title: Python molurus
summary: Python molurus is a large, nonvenomous python species native to tropical and subtropical regions of the Indian subcontinent and Southeast Asia.[3] It is known by the common names Indian python, black-tailed python,[4] Indian rock python, and Asian rock python.[5][6]  It is generally lighter colored than the Burmese python and reaches usually 3 m (9.8 ft).[7]
